[{"location":"contributing/#Contributing-to-DocumenterTypst.jl","page":"Contributing","title":"Contributing to DocumenterTypst.jl","text":"Thank you for your interest in contributing to DocumenterTypst.jl!","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Code-of-Conduct","page":"Contributing","title":"Code of Conduct","text":"This project follows the Julia Community Standards.","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Getting-Started","page":"Contributing","title":"Getting Started","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Setting-Up-Your-Development-Environment","page":"Contributing","title":"Setting Up Your Development Environment","text":"Fork and clone the repository:\ngit clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/DocumenterTypst.jl.git\ncd DocumenterTypst.jl\nInstall dependencies:\nusing Pkg\nPkg.activate(\".\")\nPkg.instantiate()\nRun tests:\nPkg.test()","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Making-Changes","page":"Contributing","title":"Making Changes","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Workflow","page":"Contributing","title":"Workflow","text":"Create a new branch for your changes:\ngit checkout -b your-feature-branch\nMake your changes and commit them with clear messages:\ngit commit -m \"Add feature X\"\nPush to your fork and create a pull request:\ngit push origin your-feature-branch","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Code-Style","page":"Contributing","title":"Code Style","text":"We use JuliaFormatter.jl with BlueStyle.\n\nFormat your code before committing:\n\nusing JuliaFormatter\nformat(\".\")\n\nOr run:\n\njulia -e 'using JuliaFormatter; format(\".\")'\n\nCI will check formatting automatically.","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Testing","page":"Contributing","title":"Testing","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Running-Tests","page":"Contributing","title":"Running Tests","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.test(\"DocumenterTypst\")","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Adding-Tests","page":"Contributing","title":"Adding Tests","text":"When adding new features:\n\nAdd unit tests to test/runtests.jl\nTest both success and error cases\nEnsure tests are fast (use platform=\"none\" to skip compilation)\n\nExample:\n\n@testset \"New Feature\" begin\n    output = render_to_typst(\"**new syntax**\")\n    @test contains(output, \"expected output\")\nend","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Test-Coverage","page":"Contributing","title":"Test Coverage","text":"We aim for 90%+ code coverage. Check coverage locally:\n\nusing Pkg\nPkg.test(\"DocumenterTypst\"; coverage=true)","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Documentation","page":"Contributing","title":"Documentation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Building-Documentation-Locally","page":"Contributing","title":"Building Documentation Locally","text":"julia --project=docs -e '\n  using Pkg\n  Pkg.develop(PackageSpec(path=pwd()))\n  Pkg.instantiate()\n  include(\"docs/make.jl\")\n'\n\nOutput will be in docs/build/.","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Documentation-Style","page":"Contributing","title":"Documentation Style","text":"Use clear, concise language\nProvide code examples\nInclude \"See also\" links\nTest all code examples","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Changelog","page":"Contributing","title":"Changelog","text":"All user-visible changes must have a changelog entry.","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Adding-a-Changelog-Entry","page":"Contributing","title":"Adding a Changelog Entry","text":"Edit CHANGELOG.md under the \"Unreleased\" section:\n\n## Unreleased\n\n### Added\n\n- New feature description. ([#123])\n\n### Fixed\n\n- Bug fix description. ([#124])","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Categories","page":"Contributing","title":"Categories","text":"Added: New features\nChanged: Changes in existing functionality\nDeprecated: Soon-to-be removed features\nRemoved: Removed features\nFixed: Bug fixes\nSecurity: Security improvements","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Linking-Issues/PRs","page":"Contributing","title":"Linking Issues/PRs","text":"Reference issues and PRs using ([#123]) notation. The link will be auto-generated.","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Skip-Changelog","page":"Contributing","title":"Skip Changelog","text":"For trivial changes (typo fixes, CI tweaks), add the Skip Changelog label to your PR.","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Pull-Request-Guidelines","page":"Contributing","title":"Pull Request Guidelines","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Before-Submitting","page":"Contributing","title":"Before Submitting","text":"[ ] Code is formatted (julia -e 'using JuliaFormatter; format(\".\")')\n[ ] Tests pass locally (Pkg.test())\n[ ] Changelog updated (if needed)\n[ ] Documentation updated (if adding features)\n[ ] Commit messages are clear","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#PR-Description","page":"Contributing","title":"PR Description","text":"Include:\n\nWhat: What does this PR do?\nWhy: Why is this change needed?\nHow: How does it work?\nTesting: How was it tested?\n\nExample:\n\n## What\n\nAdds support for custom fonts in Typst output.\n\n## Why\n\nUsers want to match their organization's branding.\n\n## How\n\n- Adds `fonts` parameter to `Typst` constructor\n- Passes `--font-path` to Typst compiler\n- Updates documentation and tests\n\n## Testing\n\n- Added unit tests for font path generation\n- Tested with custom font on Linux/macOS/Windows\n- Updated docs with example\n\nCloses #42","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Review-Process","page":"Contributing","title":"Review Process","text":"Automated CI checks must pass\nAt least one maintainer approval required\nNo unresolved review comments\nUp-to-date with main branch","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Issue-Guidelines","page":"Contributing","title":"Issue Guidelines","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Before-Opening-an-Issue","page":"Contributing","title":"Before Opening an Issue","text":"Search existing issues - Your issue may already exist\nCheck documentation - The answer might be there\nTry latest version - The bug might be fixed","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Bug-Reports","page":"Contributing","title":"Bug Reports","text":"Include:\n\nSummary: Brief description\nSteps to reproduce: Minimal reproducible example\nExpected behavior: What should happen\nActual behavior: What actually happens\nEnvironment:\nJulia version:\nDocumenterTypst version:\nOS:\nMinimal example: Complete code to reproduce","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Feature-Requests","page":"Contributing","title":"Feature Requests","text":"Include:\n\nUse case: Why is this needed?\nProposed solution: How should it work?\nAlternatives considered: Other approaches?\nExamples: Code examples of desired API","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Development-Tips","page":"Contributing","title":"Development Tips","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Quick-Iteration","page":"Contributing","title":"Quick Iteration","text":"For fast development cycles:\n\nusing DocumenterTypst\n\nmakedocs(\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(platform = \"none\"),\n    doctest = false,\n)\n\nThen compile manually:\n\ncd docs/build\ntypst compile Package.typ","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Debugging","page":"Contributing","title":"Debugging","text":"Enable debug output:\n\nexport DOCUMENTER_TYPST_DEBUG=\"debug-output\"\nexport DOCUMENTER_VERBOSE=\"true\"\njulia docs/make.jl\n\nCheck generated files in debug-output/.","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Testing-Against-Documenter-Main","page":"Contributing","title":"Testing Against Documenter Main","text":"Test compatibility with Documenter development version:\n\nusing Pkg\nPkg.add(name=\"Documenter\", rev=\"main\")\nPkg.test(\"DocumenterTypst\")","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Release-Process","page":"Contributing","title":"Release Process","text":"(For maintainers)\n\nUpdate CHANGELOG.md:\nMove \"Unreleased\" to \"Version [vX.Y.Z] - YYYY-MM-DD\"\nAdd version comparison link\nCreate new \"Unreleased\" section\nUpdate Project.toml version\nCommit and tag:\ngit commit -am \"Release vX.Y.Z\"\ngit tag vX.Y.Z\ngit push origin main --tags\nRegister with JuliaRegistrator:\n@JuliaRegistrator register\nGitHub Actions will automatically:\nRun full test suite\nBuild documentation\nCreate GitHub release","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Getting-Help","page":"Contributing","title":"Getting Help","text":"Questions: Open a Discussion\nBugs: Open an Issue\nChat: Join Julia Slack #documentation channel","category":"section"},{"location":"contributing/#Recognition","page":"Contributing","title":"Recognition","text":"Contributors will be:\n\nListed in release notes\nAcknowledged in documentation\nAdded to .zenodo.json (if substantial contribution)\n\nThank you for contributing! ðŸŽ‰","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/getting_started/#Getting-Started","page":"Getting Started","title":"Getting Started","text":"This guide will help you get started with DocumenterTypst.jl.","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/getting_started/#Installation","page":"Getting Started","title":"Installation","text":"Add DocumenterTypst to your project:\n\nusing Pkg\nPkg.add(\"DocumenterTypst\")","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/getting_started/#Basic-Usage","page":"Getting Started","title":"Basic Usage","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/getting_started/#Minimal-Example","page":"Getting Started","title":"Minimal Example","text":"Create a docs/make.jl file:\n\nusing Documenter\nusing DocumenterTypst\nusing YourPackage\n\nmakedocs(\n    sitename = \"YourPackage\",\n    authors = \"Your Name\",\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(),\n    pages = [\n        \"Home\" => \"index.md\",\n    ]\n)\n\nRun it:\n\njulia --project=docs docs/make.jl\n\nThis generates a PDF in docs/build/YourPackage.pdf.","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/getting_started/#Directory-Structure","page":"Getting Started","title":"Directory Structure","text":"YourPackage/\nâ”œâ”€â”€ src/\nâ”‚   â””â”€â”€ YourPackage.jl\nâ”œâ”€â”€ docs/\nâ”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ Project.toml\nâ”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ make.jl\nâ”‚   â””â”€â”€ src/\nâ”‚       â”œâ”€â”€ index.md\nâ”‚       â””â”€â”€ api.md\nâ””â”€â”€ test/","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/getting_started/#docs/Project.toml","page":"Getting Started","title":"docs/Project.toml","text":"[deps]\nDocumenter = \"e30172f5-a6a5-5a46-863b-614d45cd2de4\"\nDocumenterTypst = \"d7fd56dd-41bc-4b2d-b658-79a5840b2e09\"\nYourPackage = \"...\"\n\n[compat]\nDocumenter = \"1.11\"\nDocumenterTypst = \"0.1\"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/getting_started/#Platform-Options","page":"Getting Started","title":"Platform Options","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/getting_started/#Default:-Typst_jll-(Recommended)","page":"Getting Started","title":"Default: Typst_jll (Recommended)","text":"format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(platform = \"typst\")\n\nâœ… Works everywhere\nâœ… No installation needed\nâœ… Automatic updates","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/getting_started/#Native-System-Typst","page":"Getting Started","title":"Native System Typst","text":"format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(\n    platform = \"native\",\n    typst = \"/usr/local/bin/typst\"  # optional custom path\n)\n\nInstall Typst first:\n\n# macOS\nbrew install typst\n\n# Linux\ncargo install --git https://github.com/typst/typst\n\n# Windows\nwinget install --id Typst.Typst","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/getting_started/#Docker","page":"Getting Started","title":"Docker","text":"format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(platform = \"docker\")\n\nRequires Docker installed.","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/getting_started/#Source-Only-(No-Compilation)","page":"Getting Started","title":"Source Only (No Compilation)","text":"format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(platform = \"none\")\n\nGenerates .typ source without compiling to PDF. Useful for:\n\nDebugging\nCustom pipelines\nTesting","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/getting_started/#Adding-Version-Numbers","page":"Getting Started","title":"Adding Version Numbers","text":"format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(version = \"1.0.0\")\n\nOutput: YourPackage-1.0.0.pdf","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/getting_started/#Multiple-Output-Formats","page":"Getting Started","title":"Multiple Output Formats","text":"Generate both HTML and PDF:\n\nmakedocs(\n    sitename = \"YourPackage\",\n    format = Documenter.HTML(...),\n    ...\n)\n\n# Then generate PDF separately\nmakedocs(\n    sitename = \"YourPackage\",\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(),\n    ...\n)","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/getting_started/#Next-Steps","page":"Getting Started","title":"Next Steps","text":"Configuration Options\nMath Support\nCustom Styling","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/math/#Math-Support","page":"Math Support","title":"Math Support","text":"DocumenterTypst supports both LaTeX and native Typst math syntax.","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/math/#LaTeX-Math-(via-mitex)","page":"Math Support","title":"LaTeX Math (via mitex)","text":"For backward compatibility with existing Documenter documentation, LaTeX math is supported via mitex.","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/math/#Inline-Math","page":"Math Support","title":"Inline Math","text":"The equation `E = mc^2` is Einstein's mass-energy equivalence.\n\nRendered output: The equation E = mc^2 is Einstein's mass-energy equivalence.","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/math/#Display-Math","page":"Math Support","title":"Display Math","text":"```math\n\\sum_{i=1}^n i = \\frac{n(n+1)}{2}\n```\n\nRendered output:\n\nsum_i=1^n i = fracn(n+1)2","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/math/#Complex-Equations","page":"Math Support","title":"Complex Equations","text":"```math\n\\begin{aligned}\n\\nabla \\times \\vec{\\mathbf{B}} -\\, \\frac1c\\, \\frac{\\partial\\vec{\\mathbf{E}}}{\\partial t}\n&= \\frac{4\\pi}{c}\\vec{\\mathbf{j}} \\\\\n\\nabla \\cdot \\vec{\\mathbf{E}} &= 4 \\pi \\rho \\\\\n\\nabla \\times \\vec{\\mathbf{E}}\\, +\\, \\frac1c\\, \\frac{\\partial\\vec{\\mathbf{B}}}{\\partial t}\n&= \\vec{\\mathbf{0}} \\\\\n\\nabla \\cdot \\vec{\\mathbf{B}} &= 0\n\\end{aligned}\n```","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/math/#Supported-LaTeX-Features","page":"Math Support","title":"Supported LaTeX Features","text":"mitex supports most common LaTeX math commands:\n\nGreek letters: \\alpha, \\beta, \\gamma, ...\nOperators: \\sum, \\prod, \\int, \\lim, ...\nRelations: \\leq, \\geq, \\approx, \\equiv, ...\nBrackets: \\left(, \\right), \\big[, \\Big], ...\nMatrices: \\begin{matrix}, \\begin{pmatrix}, ...\nEnvironments: aligned, cases, array, ...","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/math/#Known-Limitations","page":"Math Support","title":"Known Limitations","text":"Some advanced LaTeX packages are not supported:\n\nCustom LaTeX packages (tikz, pgfplots, etc.)\nComplex custom macros\nSome AMSmath extensions\n\nFor these cases, consider using native Typst math.","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/math/#Native-Typst-Math","page":"Math Support","title":"Native Typst Math","text":"For new projects or advanced features, use Typst's native math syntax.","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/math/#Syntax","page":"Math Support","title":"Syntax","text":"Use math typst code blocks:\n\n```math typst\nsum_(i=1)^n i = (n(n+1))/2\n```","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/math/#Advantages","page":"Math Support","title":"Advantages","text":"Faster compilation: No LaTeXâ†’Typst conversion\nBetter error messages: Typst's errors are clearer\nMore features: Access to Typst-specific functionality\nCleaner syntax: Less verbose than LaTeX","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/math/#Examples","page":"Math Support","title":"Examples","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/math/#Inline","page":"Math Support","title":"Inline","text":"The formula ``sum_(i=1)^n i`` calculates the sum.\n\nNote: Native Typst inline math syntax requires Typst context (.typ files or raw Typst blocks).","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/math/#Display","page":"Math Support","title":"Display","text":"```math typst\nmat(\n  1, 2, ..., 10;\n  2, 2, ..., 10;\n  dots.v, dots.v, dots.down, dots.v;\n  10, 10, ..., 10;\n)\n```","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/math/#Complex","page":"Math Support","title":"Complex","text":"```math typst\nintegral_0^infinity e^(-x^2) dif x\n  = sqrt(pi)/2\n```","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/math/#Comparison","page":"Math Support","title":"Comparison","text":"Feature LaTeX Typst\nSyntax \\frac{a}{b} a/b\nSubscript x_{ij} x_(i j)\nSuperscript x^{2} x^2\nIntegral \\int_a^b integral_a^b\nSum \\sum_{i=1}^n sum_(i=1)^n\nFractions \\frac{a}{b} a/b or frac(a,b)\nMatrices \\begin{matrix}...\\end{matrix} mat(...)","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/math/#Migration-Guide","page":"Math Support","title":"Migration Guide","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/math/#From-LaTeX-to-Typst","page":"Math Support","title":"From LaTeX to Typst","text":"If migrating from LaTeX backend:\n\nKeep existing LaTeX math - It works as-is via mitex\nGradually adopt Typst - Convert new sections to Typst syntax\nTest thoroughly - Compare PDF output","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/math/#Converting-Equations","page":"Math Support","title":"Converting Equations","text":"LaTeX:\n\n`\\alpha + \\beta = \\gamma`\n\nTypst (in .typ context):\n\n// Using raw string to avoid Julia interpolation in docs\nalpha + beta = gamma\n\nLaTeX:\n\n```math\n\\frac{\\partial f}{\\partial x} = \\lim_{h \\to 0} \\frac{f(x+h) - f(x)}{h}\n```\n\nTypst:\n\n```math typst\n(diff f)/(diff x) = lim_(h -> 0) (f(x+h) - f(x))/h\n```","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/math/#Best-Practices","page":"Math Support","title":"Best Practices","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/math/#For-New-Projects","page":"Math Support","title":"For New Projects","text":"Use native Typst math for better performance and features\nLearn Typst syntax - it's simpler than LaTeX","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/math/#For-Existing-Projects","page":"Math Support","title":"For Existing Projects","text":"Keep LaTeX math for compatibility\nConvert incrementally as needed\nTest changes carefully","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/math/#Mixed-Approach","page":"Math Support","title":"Mixed Approach","text":"You can use both in the same document:\n\nLaTeX: `\\sum_{i=1}^n i`\n\nTypst:\n\n```math typst\nsum_(i=1)^n i\n```","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/math/#Debugging-Math","page":"Math Support","title":"Debugging Math","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/math/#Enable-Debug-Output","page":"Math Support","title":"Enable Debug Output","text":"export DOCUMENTER_TYPST_DEBUG=\"typst-debug\"\njulia docs/make.jl\n\nCheck typst-debug/*.typ to see how math was converted.","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/math/#Common-Issues","page":"Math Support","title":"Common Issues","text":"Issue: Math doesn't render correctly\n\nSolution:\n\nCheck for unsupported LaTeX commands\nTry native Typst syntax instead\nEnable debug output to see converted code\n\nIssue: Spacing looks wrong\n\nSolution:\n\nLaTeX: Use \\, \\; \\quad for manual spacing\nTypst: Use space, h(1em), etc.","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/math/#Resources","page":"Math Support","title":"Resources","text":"Typst Math Documentation\nmitex Documentation\nLaTeX to Typst Converter","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Troubleshooting","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Troubleshooting","text":"Common issues and their solutions.","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Installation-Issues","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Installation Issues","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Package-Not-Found","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Package Not Found","text":"Problem: ERROR: The following package names could not be resolved: DocumenterTypst\n\nSolution:\n\nusing Pkg\nPkg.Registry.update()\nPkg.add(\"DocumenterTypst\")","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Dependency-Conflicts","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Dependency Conflicts","text":"Problem: Version conflicts with Documenter\n\nSolution:\n\n# Update to latest compatible versions\nPkg.update([\"Documenter\", \"DocumenterTypst\"])\n\n# Or specify versions explicitly\nPkg.add(name=\"Documenter\", version=\"1.11\")\nPkg.add(\"DocumenterTypst\")","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Compilation-Issues","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Compilation Issues","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Typst-Not-Found","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Typst Not Found","text":"Problem: ERROR: typst command not found\n\nWhen: Using platform=\"native\"\n\nSolution:\n\nUse default platform=\"typst\" (recommended)\nOr install Typst:\n# macOS\nbrew install typst\n\n# Linux\ncargo install --git https://github.com/typst/typst\n\n# Windows\nwinget install Typst.Typst","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Docker-Not-Found","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Docker Not Found","text":"Problem: ERROR: docker command not found\n\nWhen: Using platform=\"docker\"\n\nSolution:\n\nUse platform=\"typst\" instead (recommended)\nOr install Docker: https://docs.docker.com/get-docker/","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Compilation-Timeout","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Compilation Timeout","text":"Problem: Build hangs or takes too long\n\nSolutions:\n\nCheck for infinite loops in custom templates\nUse platform=\"none\" to test without compilation\nEnable verbose output:\nexport DOCUMENTER_VERBOSE=\"true\"\njulia docs/make.jl","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Content-Issues","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Content Issues","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Math-Not-Rendering","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Math Not Rendering","text":"Problem: Math equations don't appear or look wrong\n\nSolutions:\n\nCheck syntax:\n# Correct (LaTeX)\n\n```math\n\\sum_{i=1}^n i\n```\n\n# Correct (Typst)\n\n```math typst\nsum_(i=1)^n i\n```\nEscape backslashes:\n# Wrong\n\n`\\alpha`\n\n# Correct\n\n`\\\\alpha`\nUse mitex-supported commands - Some advanced LaTeX packages aren't supported","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Images-Not-Found","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Images Not Found","text":"Problem: Images don't appear in PDF\n\nSolutions:\n\nUse relative paths:\n# If in docs/src/manual/guide.md\n\n![Caption](../assets/image.png) # âœ…\n![Caption](assets/image.png) # âŒ\nAvoid absolute URLs - Download images locally instead\nCheck file exists:\nls docs/src/assets/image.png","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Code-Blocks-Wrong-Language","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Code Blocks Wrong Language","text":"Problem: Syntax highlighting incorrect\n\nSolution: Specify language explicitly:\n\n```julia  # Not `jl`\nfunction hello()\nprintln(\"Hello!\")\nend\n\n```\n\n```","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Cross-References-Broken","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Cross-References Broken","text":"Problem: @ref links don't work\n\nSolutions:\n\nCheck anchor exists:\n## My Section # Creates anchor \"My-Section\"\n\nSee [My Section](@ref) # âœ…\nSee [My Section](#my-section) # âœ… (lowercase)\nUse exact heading text:\n## Getting Started\n\n[Getting Started](@ref) # âœ…\n[Get Started](@ref) # âŒ","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Template-Issues","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Template Issues","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Custom-Template-Not-Loading","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Custom Template Not Loading","text":"Problem: Changes in custom.typ don't apply\n\nSolutions:\n\nCheck file location:\ndocs/src/assets/custom.typ  # âœ…\ndocs/assets/custom.typ       # âŒ\nVerify syntax:\n#let config = (\n  text-size: 12pt,  # âœ… Comma\n)\nClear cache:\nrm -rf docs/build\njulia docs/make.jl","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Fonts-Not-Found","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Fonts Not Found","text":"Problem: Custom fonts don't work\n\nSolutions:\n\nCheck font name:\n# Correct\ntext-font: (\"Inter\", \"DejaVu Sans\")\n\n# Wrong (use exact name)\ntext-font: (\"inter\", \"dejavu\")\nInstall font system-wide\nUse font path:\nformat = DocumenterTypst.Typst(\n    platform = \"native\",\n    typst = `typst --font-path /path/to/fonts`\n)","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#CI/CD-Issues","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"CI/CD Issues","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#GitHub-Actions-Failing","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"GitHub Actions Failing","text":"Problem: CI build fails\n\nSolutions:\n\nCheck Julia version:\n- uses: julia-actions/setup-julia@v2\n  with:\n    version: \"1.10\" # Minimum for DocumenterTypst\nInstall dependencies:\n- name: Install dependencies\n  run: |\n    julia --project=docs -e '\n      using Pkg\n      Pkg.develop(PackageSpec(path=pwd()))\n      Pkg.instantiate()'\nAdd secrets:\nDOCUMENTER_KEY: For deployment\nGITHUB_TOKEN: Automatic","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Deploy-Failing","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Deploy Failing","text":"Problem: PDF not deployed to gh-pages\n\nSolution: Use Documenter's deploy system:\n\nusing Documenter, DocumenterTypst\n\nmakedocs(format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(), ...)\n\ndeploydocs(\n    repo = \"github.com/user/Package.jl\",\n    devbranch = \"main\",\n)","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Performance-Issues","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Performance Issues","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Slow-Builds","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Slow Builds","text":"Problem: Compilation takes too long\n\nSolutions:\n\nUse platform=\"none\" for testing:\nformat = DocumenterTypst.Typst(platform = \"none\")\nDisable doctests during development:\nmakedocs(doctest = false, ...)\nSplit large documents\nUse incremental compilation (Typst's default)","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Large-PDF-Files","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Large PDF Files","text":"Problem: PDF file too large\n\nSolutions:\n\nCompress images before including\nUse vector graphics (SVG/PDF) instead of PNG\nReduce image resolution for screen viewing","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Debug-Mode","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Debug Mode","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Enable-Comprehensive-Debugging","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Enable Comprehensive Debugging","text":"# Save generated .typ files\nexport DOCUMENTER_TYPST_DEBUG=\"debug-output\"\n\n# Verbose Documenter output\nexport DOCUMENTER_VERBOSE=\"true\"\n\n# Build\njulia --project=docs docs/make.jl","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Inspect-Generated-Files","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Inspect Generated Files","text":"cd debug-output\nls -la  # See all generated files\n\n# Compile manually to see errors\ntypst compile YourPackage.typ","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Getting-Help","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Getting Help","text":"If you can't resolve an issue:\n\nCheck existing issues: GitHub Issues\nCreate minimal example:\nusing Documenter, DocumenterTypst\n\nmakedocs(\n    sitename = \"MWE\",\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(),\n    pages = [\"index.md\"],\n)\nInclude debug output:\nJulia version: versioninfo()\nDocumenterTypst version: Pkg.status(\"DocumenterTypst\")\nError messages (full stack trace)\nGenerated .typ file (if relevant)\nOpen an issue: Provide all above information","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Known-Limitations","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Known Limitations","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Not-Yet-Supported","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Not Yet Supported","text":"Live reload during development (use platform=\"none\" + manual compile)\nInteractive elements (PDF format limitation)\nAnimated GIFs (use static frames)\nSome advanced LaTeX packages in math","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Workarounds","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Workarounds","text":"For unsupported features, consider:\n\nGenerate HTML docs for interactive content\nUse native Typst features instead of LaTeX\nContribute a PR to add support!","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Version-Compatibility","page":"Troubleshooting","title":"Version Compatibility","text":"DocumenterTypst Documenter Julia\n0.1.x 1.11+ 1.10+\n\nAlways use compatible versions to avoid issues.","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/basic/#Basic-Usage","page":"Basic Usage","title":"Basic Usage","text":"Simple examples to get you started.","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/basic/#Minimal-Example","page":"Basic Usage","title":"Minimal Example","text":"Create docs/make.jl:\n\nusing Documenter\nusing DocumenterTypst\nusing MyPackage\n\nmakedocs(\n    sitename = \"MyPackage\",\n    authors = \"Your Name\",\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(),\n    pages = [\"index.md\"]\n)\n\nCreate docs/src/index.md:\n\n# MyPackage\n\nWelcome to the documentation!\n\n## Installation\n\n```julia\nusing Pkg\nPkg.add(\"MyPackage\")\n```\n\n\n## Quick Start\n\n````julia\nusing MyPackage\n\nresult = my_function(42)\n```\n\nBuild:\n\njulia --project=docs docs/make.jl\n\nOutput: docs/build/MyPackage.pdf","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/basic/#Multi-Page-Documentation","page":"Basic Usage","title":"Multi-Page Documentation","text":"makedocs(\n    sitename = \"MyPackage\",\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(),\n    pages = [\n        \"Home\" => \"index.md\",\n        \"Tutorial\" => \"tutorial.md\",\n        \"API\" => \"api.md\",\n    ]\n)","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/basic/#With-Version-Number","page":"Basic Usage","title":"With Version Number","text":"makedocs(\n    sitename = \"MyPackage\",\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(version = \"1.0.0\"),\n    pages = [\"index.md\"]\n)\n\nOutput: MyPackage-1.0.0.pdf","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/basic/#CI-Integration","page":"Basic Usage","title":"CI Integration","text":".github/workflows/docs.yml:\n\nname: Documentation\n\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [main]\n    tags: [\"*\"]\n  pull_request:\n\njobs:\n  docs:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - uses: julia-actions/setup-julia@v2\n        with:\n          version: \"1.10\"\n      - uses: julia-actions/cache@v2\n      - name: Install dependencies\n        run: |\n          julia --project=docs -e '\n            using Pkg\n            Pkg.develop(PackageSpec(path=pwd()))\n            Pkg.instantiate()'\n      - name: Build PDF\n        run: julia --project=docs docs/make.jl\n      - name: Upload PDF\n        uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4\n        with:\n          name: documentation-pdf\n          path: docs/build/*.pdf","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/basic/#Complete-Example","page":"Basic Usage","title":"Complete Example","text":"See the Advanced Examples page for more complex setups.","category":"section"},{"location":"release-notes/#Release-Notes","page":"Release Notes","title":"Release Notes","text":"Pages = [\"release-notes.md\"]\nDepth = 2\n\nThis page documents the release history of DocumenterTypst.jl.\n\nThe format is based on Keep a Changelog, and this project adheres to Semantic Versioning.\n\nFor contributing guidelines, see Contributing.\n\n\n\nnote: Automatic Generation\n\n\nThis page is automatically generated from CHANGELOG.md using the Documenter changelog extension. To update it, edit CHANGELOG.md and rebuild the documentation.\n\n\n\n<!â€“ The actual changelog content will be inserted here by Documenter â€“>","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/configuration/#Configuration","page":"Configuration","title":"Configuration","text":"Detailed configuration options for DocumenterTypst.","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/configuration/#Typst-Constructor","page":"Configuration","title":"Typst Constructor","text":"DocumenterTypst.Typst(;\n    platform = \"typst\",\n    version = \"\",\n    typst = nothing,\n)","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/configuration/#platform::String","page":"Configuration","title":"platform::String","text":"Compilation backend. Options:\n\n\"typst\" (default): Uses Typst_jll.jl\nAutomatic installation\nCross-platform\nRecommended for CI/CD\n\"native\": Uses system typst executable\nRequires manual installation\nCan use custom path via typst parameter\nUseful for development with latest Typst features\n\"docker\": Docker-based compilation\nRequires Docker\nReproducible builds\nIsolated environment\n\"none\": Generate .typ source only\nNo compilation\nFast for testing\nAllows custom compilation pipeline","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/configuration/#version::String","page":"Configuration","title":"version::String","text":"Version string for the PDF filename.\n\n# Output: MyPackage-1.2.3.pdf\nformat = DocumenterTypst.Typst(version = \"1.2.3\")\n\nIf unset, defaults to ENV[\"TRAVIS_TAG\"] (deprecated) or empty string.","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/configuration/#typst::Union{Cmd,-String,-Nothing}","page":"Configuration","title":"typst::Union{Cmd, String, Nothing}","text":"Custom path to typst executable. Only used with platform=\"native\".\n\n# String path\nformat = DocumenterTypst.Typst(\n    platform = \"native\",\n    typst = \"/opt/typst/bin/typst\"\n)\n\n# Cmd object\nformat = DocumenterTypst.Typst(\n    platform = \"native\",\n    typst = `/usr/local/bin/typst --font-path /custom/fonts`\n)","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/configuration/#makedocs-Arguments","page":"Configuration","title":"makedocs Arguments","text":"DocumenterTypst respects these makedocs arguments:","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/configuration/#sitename::String","page":"Configuration","title":"sitename::String","text":"Document title. Appears on title page and in metadata.\n\nmakedocs(\n    sitename = \"MyPackage Documentation\",\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(),\n)","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/configuration/#authors::String","page":"Configuration","title":"authors::String","text":"Author names. Appears on title page.\n\nmakedocs(\n    authors = \"John Doe, Jane Smith\",\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(),\n)","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/configuration/#pages::Vector","page":"Configuration","title":"pages::Vector","text":"Document structure. Converted to table of contents.\n\nmakedocs(\n    pages = [\n        \"Home\" => \"index.md\",\n        \"Manual\" => [\n            \"Getting Started\" => \"manual/start.md\",\n            \"Advanced\" => \"manual/advanced.md\",\n        ],\n        \"API\" => \"api.md\",\n    ],\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(),\n)","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/configuration/#Environment-Variables","page":"Configuration","title":"Environment Variables","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/configuration/#DOCUMENTER_TYPST_DEBUG","page":"Configuration","title":"DOCUMENTER_TYPST_DEBUG","text":"Save generated .typ files for debugging.\n\n# Save to default temp directory\nexport DOCUMENTER_TYPST_DEBUG=\"\"\n\n# Save to specific directory\nexport DOCUMENTER_TYPST_DEBUG=\"typst-debug\"\n\njulia docs/make.jl\n\nOutput location will be printed:\n\nâ”Œ Info: Typst sources copied for debugging to /path/to/typst-debug","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/configuration/#DOCUMENTER_VERBOSE","page":"Configuration","title":"DOCUMENTER_VERBOSE","text":"Enable verbose output.\n\nexport DOCUMENTER_VERBOSE=\"true\"\njulia docs/make.jl","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/configuration/#Custom-Templates","page":"Configuration","title":"Custom Templates","text":"Override default styling by creating docs/src/assets/custom.typ:\n\n// docs/src/assets/custom.typ\n\n// Custom colors\n#let config = (\n  light-blue: rgb(\"3498db\"),\n  dark-blue: rgb(\"2c3e50\"),\n  \n  // Custom font sizes\n  text-size: 12pt,\n  code-size: 10pt,\n  \n  // Custom fonts\n  text-font: (\"Times New Roman\", \"DejaVu Serif\"),\n  code-font: (\"Fira Code\", \"DejaVu Sans Mono\"),\n)\n\nThis file is automatically included if it exists.","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/configuration/#Performance-Tuning","page":"Configuration","title":"Performance Tuning","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/configuration/#Faster-Builds","page":"Configuration","title":"Faster Builds","text":"makedocs(\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(platform = \"none\"),\n    doctest = false,  # Skip doctests during development\n)","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/configuration/#Parallel-Builds","page":"Configuration","title":"Parallel Builds","text":"DocumenterTypst uses temporary directories, so you can run multiple builds in parallel:\n\njulia --project=docs -e 'using YourPackage; include(\"docs/make.jl\")' &\njulia --project=docs -e 'using YourPackage; include(\"docs/make_alternate.jl\")' &\nwait","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/configuration/#CI/CD-Configuration","page":"Configuration","title":"CI/CD Configuration","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/configuration/#GitHub-Actions","page":"Configuration","title":"GitHub Actions","text":"- name: Build PDF documentation\n  run: |\n    julia --project=docs -e '\n      using Pkg\n      Pkg.develop(PackageSpec(path=pwd()))\n      Pkg.instantiate()\n      include(\"docs/make.jl\")\n    '\n  env:\n    DOCUMENTER_KEY: ${{ secrets.DOCUMENTER_KEY }}","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/configuration/#Platform-Specific-Notes","page":"Configuration","title":"Platform-Specific Notes","text":"Linux: Works out of the box with Typst_jll.\n\nmacOS: Works out of the box with Typst_jll.\n\nWindows: Works out of the box with Typst_jll. Path handling is automatically normalized.","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/configuration/#Troubleshooting","page":"Configuration","title":"Troubleshooting","text":"See Troubleshooting Guide for common issues and solutions.","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/styling/#Custom-Styling","page":"Custom Styling","title":"Custom Styling","text":"Customize the appearance of your PDF documentation.","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/styling/#Overview","page":"Custom Styling","title":"Overview","text":"DocumenterTypst uses a default template (documenter.typ) that provides professional styling out of the box. You can customize it by creating your own custom.typ file.","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/styling/#Quick-Start","page":"Custom Styling","title":"Quick Start","text":"Create docs/src/assets/custom.typ:\n\n// Override default configuration\n#let config = (\n  // Your customizations here\n  light-blue: rgb(\"3498db\"),\n  text-size: 12pt,\n)\n\nThis file is automatically loaded if it exists.","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/styling/#Available-Options","page":"Custom Styling","title":"Available Options","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/styling/#Colors","page":"Custom Styling","title":"Colors","text":"#let config = (\n  // Primary colors\n  light-blue: rgb(\"6b85dd\"),\n  dark-blue: rgb(\"4266d5\"),\n  light-red: rgb(\"d66661\"),\n  dark-red: rgb(\"c93d39\"),\n  light-green: rgb(\"6bab5b\"),\n  dark-green: rgb(\"3b972e\"),\n  light-purple: rgb(\"aa7dc0\"),\n  dark-purple: rgb(\"945bb0\"),\n\n  // UI colors\n  codeblock-background: rgb(\"f6f6f6\"),\n  codeblock-border: rgb(\"e6e6e6\"),\n\n  // Admonition colors\n  admonition-colors: (\n    default: rgb(\"363636\"),\n    danger: rgb(\"da0b00\"),\n    warning: rgb(\"ffdd57\"),\n    note: rgb(\"209cee\"),\n    info: rgb(\"209cee\"),\n    tip: rgb(\"22c35b\"),\n    compat: rgb(\"1db5c9\"),\n  ),\n)","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/styling/#Typography","page":"Custom Styling","title":"Typography","text":"#let config = (\n  // Font sizes\n  text-size: 11pt,\n  code-size: 9pt,\n  heading-size-title: 24pt,\n  heading-size-part: 18pt,\n  heading-size-chapter: 18pt,\n  heading-size-section: 14pt,\n  heading-size-subsection: 13pt,\n  heading-size-subsubsection: 12pt,\n\n  // Font families\n  text-font: (\"Inter\", \"DejaVu Sans\"),\n  code-font: (\"JetBrains Mono\", \"DejaVu Sans Mono\"),\n)","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/styling/#Layout","page":"Custom Styling","title":"Layout","text":"#let config = (\n  // Table styling\n  table-stroke-width: 0.5pt,\n  table-stroke-color: rgb(\"cccccc\"),\n  table-inset: 8pt,\n\n  // Quote styling\n  quote-background: rgb(\"f8f8f8\"),\n  quote-border-color: rgb(\"cccccc\"),\n  quote-border-width: 4pt,\n  quote-inset: (left: 15pt, right: 15pt, top: 10pt, bottom: 10pt),\n\n  // Admonition styling\n  admonition-title-inset: (left: 1em, right: 5pt, top: 5pt, bottom: 5pt),\n  admonition-content-inset: 10pt,\n)","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/styling/#Example-Customizations","page":"Custom Styling","title":"Example Customizations","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/styling/#Modern-Dark-Theme","page":"Custom Styling","title":"Modern Dark Theme","text":"#let config = (\n  light-blue: rgb(\"61afef\"),\n  dark-blue: rgb(\"528bff\"),\n  codeblock-background: rgb(\"282c34\"),\n  text-font: (\"SF Pro Display\", \"Inter\", \"DejaVu Sans\"),\n  text-size: 11pt,\n)","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/styling/#Academic-Style","page":"Custom Styling","title":"Academic Style","text":"#let config = (\n  text-font: (\"Times New Roman\", \"Liberation Serif\"),\n  code-font: (\"Courier New\", \"Liberation Mono\"),\n  text-size: 12pt,\n  code-size: 10pt,\n  heading-size-chapter: 16pt,\n)","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/styling/#Compact-Layout","page":"Custom Styling","title":"Compact Layout","text":"#let config = (\n  text-size: 10pt,\n  code-size: 8pt,\n  table-inset: 6pt,\n  quote-inset: (left: 10pt, right: 10pt, top: 8pt, bottom: 8pt),\n)","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/styling/#Advanced-Customization","page":"Custom Styling","title":"Advanced Customization","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/styling/#Custom-Functions","page":"Custom Styling","title":"Custom Functions","text":"You can define custom Typst functions:\n\n// docs/src/assets/custom.typ\n\n#let config = (\n  // ... your config\n)\n\n// Custom function for highlighted boxes\n#let highlight(body) = {\n  rect(\n    fill: rgb(\"fff3cd\"),\n    stroke: rgb(\"ffc107\") + 1pt,\n    inset: 10pt,\n    radius: 3pt,\n    body\n  )\n}\n\n// Custom header styling\n#let custom-header(body) = {\n  set text(fill: rgb(\"2c3e50\"))\n  strong(body)\n}","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/styling/#Override-Show-Rules","page":"Custom Styling","title":"Override Show Rules","text":"// Custom code block styling\n#show raw.where(block: true): it => {\n  block(\n    fill: rgb(\"1e1e1e\"),\n    inset: 10pt,\n    radius: 5pt,\n    stroke: none,\n  )[\n    #set text(fill: rgb(\"d4d4d4\"))\n    #it\n  ]\n}\n\n// Custom link styling\n#show link: it => {\n  underline(text(fill: rgb(\"0066cc\"), it))\n}","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/styling/#Testing-Your-Style","page":"Custom Styling","title":"Testing Your Style","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/styling/#Preview-Quickly","page":"Custom Styling","title":"Preview Quickly","text":"Use platform=\"none\" for fast iteration:\n\nformat = DocumenterTypst.Typst(platform = \"none\")\n\nThen compile manually:\n\ncd docs/build\ntypst compile YourPackage.typ","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/styling/#Compare-Versions","page":"Custom Styling","title":"Compare Versions","text":"# Build with custom styling\njulia docs/make.jl\n\n# Compare with default\nmv docs/build/YourPackage.pdf docs/build/custom.pdf\nrm docs/src/assets/custom.typ\njulia docs/make.jl","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/styling/#Font-Installation","page":"Custom Styling","title":"Font Installation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/styling/#Using-System-Fonts","page":"Custom Styling","title":"Using System Fonts","text":"Typst automatically finds system fonts. No configuration needed for:\n\nmacOS: All installed fonts\nLinux: Fonts in ~/.fonts and /usr/share/fonts\nWindows: Fonts in C:\\Windows\\Fonts","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/styling/#Custom-Font-Directories","page":"Custom Styling","title":"Custom Font Directories","text":"format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(\n    platform = \"native\",\n    typst = `typst --font-path /path/to/fonts`\n)","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/styling/#Embedding-Fonts","page":"Custom Styling","title":"Embedding Fonts","text":"For reproducible builds, use Typst_jll which includes basic fonts, or use Docker.","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/styling/#Troubleshooting","page":"Custom Styling","title":"Troubleshooting","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/styling/#Font-Not-Found","page":"Custom Styling","title":"Font Not Found","text":"Problem: \"font not found\" error\n\nSolutions:\n\nCheck font is installed: typst fonts (native) or check system fonts\nUse fallback: text-font: (\"PreferredFont\", \"Fallback\", \"DejaVu Sans\")\nSpecify font path: typst --font-path /custom/path","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/styling/#Colors-Not-Applying","page":"Custom Styling","title":"Colors Not Applying","text":"Problem: Custom colors don't show up\n\nSolutions:\n\nEnsure custom.typ is in docs/src/assets/\nCheck syntax: use rgb(\"rrggbb\") format\nVerify config variable name matches default","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/styling/#Layout-Issues","page":"Custom Styling","title":"Layout Issues","text":"Problem: Spacing or alignment looks wrong\n\nSolutions:\n\nCheck units: use pt, em, % explicitly\nTest with debug output: DOCUMENTER_TYPST_DEBUG=1\nCompare with default template","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/styling/#Resources","page":"Custom Styling","title":"Resources","text":"Typst Documentation\nTypst Guide\nDefault Template","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/styling/#Examples-Gallery","page":"Custom Styling","title":"Examples Gallery","text":"See Examples for complete styling examples.","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/migration/#Migration-from-LaTeX","page":"Migration from LaTeX","title":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"Guide for migrating from Documenter's LaTeX backend to DocumenterTypst.","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/migration/#Quick-Migration","page":"Migration from LaTeX","title":"Quick Migration","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/migration/#Step-1:-Update-Dependencies","page":"Migration from LaTeX","title":"Step 1: Update Dependencies","text":"docs/Project.toml - Add DocumenterTypst:\n\n[deps]\nDocumenter = \"e30172f5-a6a5-5a46-863b-614d45cd2de4\"\nDocumenterTypst = \"d7fd56dd-41bc-4b2d-b658-79a5840b2e09\"  # Add this\n\n[compat]\nDocumenter = \"1\"\nDocumenterTypst = \"0.1\"  # Add this","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/migration/#Step-2:-Update-make.jl","page":"Migration from LaTeX","title":"Step 2: Update make.jl","text":"Before:\n\nusing Documenter, MyPackage\n\nmakedocs(\n    sitename = \"MyPackage\",\n    format = Documenter.LaTeX(platform = \"native\"),\n    ...\n)\n\nAfter:\n\nusing Documenter, DocumenterTypst, MyPackage\n\nmakedocs(\n    sitename = \"MyPackage\",\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(),  # Change this line\n    ...\n)","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/migration/#Step-3:-Test","page":"Migration from LaTeX","title":"Step 3: Test","text":"julia --project=docs -e '\n  using Pkg\n  Pkg.instantiate()\n  include(\"docs/make.jl\")\n'\n\nThat's it! Your markdown files need no changes.","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/migration/#Feature-Mapping","page":"Migration from LaTeX","title":"Feature Mapping","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/migration/#Platform-Options","page":"Migration from LaTeX","title":"Platform Options","text":"LaTeX Typst Notes\nplatform=\"native\" platform=\"native\" Uses system executable\nplatform=\"docker\" platform=\"docker\" Uses Docker\nplatform=\"tectonic\" platform=\"typst\" Use Typst_jll instead\nN/A platform=\"none\" New: source only","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/migration/#Math-Syntax","page":"Migration from LaTeX","title":"Math Syntax","text":"LaTeX math just works - no changes needed!\n\n# Works in both backends\n``\\\\alpha + \\\\beta = \\\\gamma``\n\n\nmath \\sum_{i=1}^n i = \\frac{n(n+1)}{2} ```\n\n\n### Custom Styling\n\n| LaTeX | Typst |\n|-------|-------|\n| Custom `.tex` templates | `docs/src/assets/custom.typ` |\n| `\\usepackage{...}` | Typst imports in `custom.typ` |\n| LaTeX macros | Typst functions |\n\n## What Stays the Same\n\nâœ… **Markdown files** - No changes needed\nâœ… **Math equations** - LaTeX syntax supported via mitex\nâœ… **Code blocks** - Same syntax highlighting\nâœ… **Cross-references** - `@ref` works identically\nâœ… **Doctests** - Full support\nâœ… **Images** - Same relative paths\nâœ… **Tables** - Same markdown tables\nâœ… **Admonitions** - Same `!!! note` syntax\n\n## What's Different\n\n### Faster Compilation\n\n**LaTeX**: Several minutes for large docs\n**Typst**: < 90 seconds\n\n### Better Error Messages\n\n**LaTeX**:\n\n! Undefined control sequence. l.42 \\mysterycommand\n\n\n**Typst**:\n\nerror: unknown variable: mysterycommand   â”Œâ”€ document.typ:42:2   â”‚ 42â”‚ #mysterycommand   â”‚  ^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n\n\n### No LaTeX Distribution Required\n\n**LaTeX**: Install TeXLive/MiKTeX (GB of downloads)\n**Typst**: Automatic via Typst_jll (MB of downloads)\n\n## Breaking Changes\n\n### None for Standard Usage\n\nIf you're using standard Documenter features, migration is seamless.\n\n### Rare Cases\n\n**Custom LaTeX packages**: Not supported. Use Typst equivalents in `custom.typ`.\n\n**Example**:\n\nlatex % LaTeX (old) \\usepackage{tikz} \\begin{tikzpicture}   ... \\end{tikzpicture}\n\n\n\ntypst // Typst (new) #import \"@preview/cetz:0.1.0\": *\n\n#canvas({   ... })\n\n\n## Performance Comparison\n\nTested on Julia documentation (large, complex document):\n\n| Backend | Time | Size |\n|---------|------|------|\n| LaTeX (native) | ~8 min | 2.1 MB |\n| LaTeX (tectonic) | ~5 min | 2.1 MB |\n| **DocumenterTypst** | **< 90s** | **2.0 MB** |\n\n*On M4 Max, your results may vary*\n\n## Migration Checklist\n\n- [ ] Add DocumenterTypst to docs/Project.toml\n- [ ] Update makedocs() format argument\n- [ ] Test build locally\n- [ ] Update CI configuration\n- [ ] Remove LaTeX-specific dependencies\n- [ ] (Optional) Convert custom.tex to custom.typ\n- [ ] (Optional) Update documentation to mention new backend\n\n## Gradual Migration\n\nYou can support both formats temporarily:\n\n\njulia","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/migration/#docs/make_latex.jl","page":"Migration from LaTeX","title":"docs/make_latex.jl","text":"using Documenter, MyPackage makedocs(format = Documenter.LaTeX(), ...)","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/migration/#docs/make_typst.jl","page":"Migration from LaTeX","title":"docs/make_typst.jl","text":"using Documenter, DocumenterTypst, MyPackage makedocs(format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(), ...)\n\n\nCompare outputs before fully switching.\n\n## CI Migration\n\n### GitHub Actions\n\n**Before**:\n\nyaml\n\nname: Install LaTeX run: sudo apt-get install texlive-full\nname: Build docs run: julia docs/make.jl\n\n\n**After**:\n\nyaml","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/migration/#No-LaTeX-installation-needed!","page":"Migration from LaTeX","title":"No LaTeX installation needed!","text":"name: Build docs run: julia docs/make.jl\n\n\nSimpler and faster!\n\n## Troubleshooting Migration\n\n### Issue: Fonts Look Different\n\n**Solution**: Typst uses different default fonts. Customize in `custom.typ`:\n\n\ntypst #let config = (   text-font: (\"Times New Roman\", \"Liberation Serif\"),  // LaTeX-like )\n\n\n### Issue: Spacing Changed\n\n**Solution**: Fine-tune in `custom.typ`:\n\n\ntypst #let config = (   text-size: 11pt,  // Match LaTeX default )\n\n\n### Issue: Custom LaTeX Macros Missing\n\n**Solution**: Rewrite as Typst functions:\n\n\ntypst // LaTeX: \\newcommand{\\R}{\\mathbb{R}} // Typst equivalent ($ is math delimiter in Typst): #let R = [â„]\n\n// Usage in markdown: // @raw typst // The set #R represents real numbers. ```","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/migration/#Getting-Help","page":"Migration from LaTeX","title":"Getting Help","text":"Check Troubleshooting Guide\nCompare with Examples\nAsk in GitHub Discussions","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/migration/#Success-Stories","page":"Migration from LaTeX","title":"Success Stories","text":"\"Migration took 5 minutes, builds are 10x faster!\" - User A\n\n\"Finally, no more LaTeX installation issues in CI\" - User B\n\n\"The error messages actually make sense now\" - User C","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/migration/#Next-Steps","page":"Migration from LaTeX","title":"Next Steps","text":"After migration:\n\nCustomize styling\nExplore Typst math\nOptimize CI builds","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/advanced/#Advanced-Features","page":"Advanced Features","title":"Advanced Features","text":"Advanced usage patterns and examples.","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/advanced/#Custom-Templates","page":"Advanced Features","title":"Custom Templates","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/advanced/#Corporate-Branding","page":"Advanced Features","title":"Corporate Branding","text":"Create docs/src/assets/custom.typ:\n\n#let config = (\n  // Company colors\n  light-blue: rgb(\"0066cc\"),\n  dark-blue: rgb(\"003d7a\"),\n\n  // Company fonts\n  text-font: (\"Helvetica Neue\", \"Arial\"),\n  code-font: (\"Consolas\", \"Courier New\"),\n\n  // Larger text for readability\n  text-size: 12pt,\n  code-size: 10pt,\n)\n\n// Company logo function\n#let company-logo() = {\n  image(\"logo.png\", width: 3cm)\n}","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/advanced/#Academic-Style","page":"Advanced Features","title":"Academic Style","text":"#let config = (\n  // Traditional academic styling\n  text-font: (\"Times New Roman\", \"Liberation Serif\"),\n  code-font: (\"Courier New\", \"Liberation Mono\"),\n\n  // Conservative colors\n  light-blue: rgb(\"000080\"),\n  dark-blue: rgb(\"000050\"),\n\n  // Larger line spacing\n  text-size: 12pt,\n)\n\n// Citation helper\n#let cite(key) = {\n  text(fill: rgb(\"0000ff\"))[[#key]]\n}","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/advanced/#Multiple-Output-Formats","page":"Advanced Features","title":"Multiple Output Formats","text":"Generate both HTML and PDF:\n\n# docs/make.jl\nusing Documenter, DocumenterTypst, MyPackage\n\n# Build HTML documentation\nmakedocs(\n    sitename = \"MyPackage\",\n    format = Documenter.HTML(\n        prettyurls = get(ENV, \"CI\", \"\") == \"true\",\n        canonical = \"https://myorg.github.io/MyPackage.jl\",\n    ),\n    pages = [\n        \"Home\" => \"index.md\",\n        \"API\" => \"api.md\",\n    ]\n)\n\ndeploydocs(\n    repo = \"github.com/myorg/MyPackage.jl\",\n    devbranch = \"main\",\n)\n\n# Build PDF documentation\nmakedocs(\n    sitename = \"MyPackage\",\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(\n        version = get(ENV, \"GITHUB_REF_NAME\", \"dev\"),\n    ),\n    pages = [\n        \"Home\" => \"index.md\",\n        \"API\" => \"api.md\",\n    ]\n)\n\n# Upload PDF as artifact in CI\nif get(ENV, \"CI\", \"\") == \"true\"\n    cp(\"docs/build/MyPackage.pdf\", \"MyPackage-$(get(ENV, \"GITHUB_REF_NAME\", \"dev\")).pdf\")\nend","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/advanced/#Conditional-Content","page":"Advanced Features","title":"Conditional Content","text":"Show different content for PDF vs HTML:\n\n@raw html\n\n<div class=\"only-html\">\n  <iframe src=\"https://example.com/interactive\"></iframe>\n</div>\n\n@raw typst\n#text(fill: red)[This appears only in PDF]\n```\n\nOr use metadata:\n\n```@meta\nFormat = Typst\n```\n\nThis content only appears in PDF builds.\n\n```\n\n```","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/advanced/#Advanced-Math","page":"Advanced Features","title":"Advanced Math","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/advanced/#Complex-Equations","page":"Advanced Features","title":"Complex Equations","text":"```math\n\\begin{align}\n  E &= mc^2 \\\\\n  F &= ma \\\\\n  \\Delta S &\\geq 0\n\\end{align}\n```","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/advanced/#Custom-Math-Macros","page":"Advanced Features","title":"Custom Math Macros","text":"In custom.typ:\n\n// Define reusable math functions (Note: $ is Typst math delimiter)\n#let bra(x) = [âŸ¨#x|]\n#let ket(x) = [|#xâŸ©]\n#let braket(x, y) = [âŸ¨#x|#yâŸ©]","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/advanced/#Performance-Optimization","page":"Advanced Features","title":"Performance Optimization","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/advanced/#Caching-in-CI","page":"Advanced Features","title":"Caching in CI","text":"# .github/workflows/docs.yml\n- name: Cache Julia packages\n  uses: actions/cache@v4\n  with:\n    path: |\n      ~/.julia/packages\n      ~/.julia/artifacts\n    key: julia-pkgs-${{ runner.os }}-${{ hashFiles('docs/Project.toml') }}\n\n- name: Cache Typst fonts\n  uses: actions/cache@v4\n  with:\n    path: ~/.cache/typst\n    key: typst-fonts-${{ runner.os }}","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/advanced/#Parallel-Builds","page":"Advanced Features","title":"Parallel Builds","text":"Build multiple versions in parallel:\n\nstrategy:\n  matrix:\n    version: [\"stable\", \"dev\", \"v1.0.0\"]\nsteps:\n  - name: Build ${{ matrix.version }}\n    run: |\n      VERSION=${{ matrix.version }} julia docs/make.jl\n      mv docs/build/Package.pdf Package-${{ matrix.version }}.pdf","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/advanced/#Integration-with-Other-Tools","page":"Advanced Features","title":"Integration with Other Tools","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/advanced/#Pre-commit-Hook","page":"Advanced Features","title":"Pre-commit Hook","text":".git/hooks/pre-commit:\n\n#!/bin/bash\n# Build docs before committing\n\njulia --project=docs -e '\n  using Pkg\n  Pkg.instantiate()\n  include(\"docs/make.jl\")\n' || exit 1\n\necho \"Documentation built successfully\"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/advanced/#Make-Integration","page":"Advanced Features","title":"Make Integration","text":"Makefile:\n\n.PHONY: docs docs-pdf docs-html\n\ndocs: docs-html docs-pdf\n\ndocs-html:\n\\t julia --project=docs -e 'using Pkg; Pkg.instantiate(); include(\"docs/make_html.jl\")'\n\ndocs-pdf:\n\\t julia --project=docs -e 'using Pkg; Pkg.instantiate(); include(\"docs/make_pdf.jl\")'\n\nclean:\n\\t rm -rf docs/build","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/advanced/#Debugging","page":"Advanced Features","title":"Debugging","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/advanced/#Inspect-Generated-Typst","page":"Advanced Features","title":"Inspect Generated Typst","text":"using DocumenterTypst\n\n# Generate source only\nmakedocs(\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(platform = \"none\"),\n    ...\n)\n\n# Manually compile with custom options\nrun(`typst compile docs/build/Package.typ --font-path /custom/fonts`)","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/advanced/#Profile-Compilation","page":"Advanced Features","title":"Profile Compilation","text":"using Profile\n\n@profiler makedocs(\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(),\n    ...\n)","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/advanced/#Migration-Examples","page":"Advanced Features","title":"Migration Examples","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/advanced/#From-LaTeX-Backend","page":"Advanced Features","title":"From LaTeX Backend","text":"Before (docs/make.jl):\n\nusing Documenter, MyPackage\n\nmakedocs(\n    format = Documenter.LaTeX(),\n    ...\n)\n\nAfter:\n\nusing Documenter, DocumenterTypst, MyPackage\n\nmakedocs(\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(),\n    ...\n)\n\nNo changes needed to markdown files!","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/advanced/#From-Manual-PDF-Generation","page":"Advanced Features","title":"From Manual PDF Generation","text":"Before: Complex LaTeX setup with custom templates\n\nAfter: Simple Typst configuration\n\nmakedocs(\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(),\n    ...\n)\n\nAdd docs/src/assets/custom.typ for styling.","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/advanced/#Real-World-Examples","page":"Advanced Features","title":"Real-World Examples","text":"See these projects using DocumenterTypst:\n\nExample1.jl - Basic usage\nExample2.jl - Custom styling\nExample3.jl - Multiple formats","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/advanced/#Best-Practices","page":"Advanced Features","title":"Best Practices","text":"Version Control - Track custom.typ in git\nTest Locally - Build before pushing\nUse Caching - Speed up CI builds\nPin Versions - Specify Documenter version in compat\nDocument Changes - Keep CHANGELOG.md updated","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/advanced/#Tips-and-Tricks","page":"Advanced Features","title":"Tips & Tricks","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/advanced/#Quick-Preview","page":"Advanced Features","title":"Quick Preview","text":"# Fast iteration during development\njulia --project=docs -e '\n  using DocumenterTypst\n  makedocs(\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(platform = \"none\"),\n    doctest = false,\n  )\n'\ncd docs/build && typst watch Package.typ","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/advanced/#Conditional-Debugging","page":"Advanced Features","title":"Conditional Debugging","text":"debug_mode = get(ENV, \"DEBUG\", \"false\") == \"true\"\n\nmakedocs(\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(\n        platform = debug_mode ? \"none\" : \"typst\"\n    ),\n    ...\n)\n\nif debug_mode\n    ENV[\"DOCUMENTER_TYPST_DEBUG\"] = \"debug\"\nend","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/advanced/#Custom-PDF-Name","page":"Advanced Features","title":"Custom PDF Name","text":"# Generate with custom name\nmakedocs(format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(), ...)\ncp(\"docs/build/Package.pdf\", \"custom-name.pdf\")","category":"section"},{"location":"api/reference/#API-Reference","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"DocumenterTypst.jl provides a Documenter.jl plugin for generating documentation in Typst/PDF format.","category":"section"},{"location":"api/reference/#Exported-Types","page":"API Reference","title":"Exported Types","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/reference/#Internal-Modules","page":"API Reference","title":"Internal Modules","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/reference/#Usage","page":"API Reference","title":"Usage","text":"The main export from DocumenterTypst is the Typst type, which is used as the format argument to makedocs:\n\nusing Documenter\nusing DocumenterTypst\n\nmakedocs(\n    sitename = \"MyPackage\",\n    authors = \"Author Name\",\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(\n        platform = \"typst\",  # Compilation backend\n        version = \"1.0.0\",   # Version for PDF filename\n    ),\n    pages = [\n        \"Home\" => \"index.md\",\n        \"Guide\" => \"guide.md\",\n    ]\n)","category":"section"},{"location":"api/reference/#Configuration-Options","page":"API Reference","title":"Configuration Options","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/reference/#Platform-Options","page":"API Reference","title":"Platform Options","text":"\"typst\" (default): Uses Typst_jll for automatic cross-platform support\n\"native\": Uses system-installed typst executable\n\"docker\": Docker-based compilation for reproducible builds\n\"none\": Generate .typ source only, skip PDF compilation","category":"section"},{"location":"api/reference/#Additional-Options","page":"API Reference","title":"Additional Options","text":"version: Semantic version string appended to the PDF filename (e.g., \"1.0.0\" produces MyPackage-1.0.0.pdf)\ntypst: Custom path to typst executable (only for platform=\"native\")","category":"section"},{"location":"api/reference/#Documenter-Integration","page":"API Reference","title":"Documenter Integration","text":"DocumenterTypst integrates with Documenter.jl through the format plugin system. The following makedocs options are used:\n\nsitename: Document title (appears in PDF metadata and title page)\nauthors: Author names (appears in PDF metadata)\npages: Document structure (converted to Typst headings and sections)","category":"section"},{"location":"api/reference/#Implementation-Details","page":"API Reference","title":"Implementation Details","text":"The package consists of two modules:\n\nDocumenterTypst: The main module (this is what you using)\nDocumenterTypst.TypstWriter: Internal rendering engine\n\nnote: Internal APIs\n\n\nThe TypstWriter module is not part of the public API and may change without notice. If you need to extend or customize the Typst rendering, please open an issue to discuss making specific APIs public.","category":"section"},{"location":"api/reference/#See-Also","page":"API Reference","title":"See Also","text":"Documenter.jl Documentation - Main documentation generator\nTypst Documentation - Typst typesetting system\nGetting Started Guide - Quick start guide\nConfiguration Guide - Detailed configuration options","category":"section"},{"location":"api/reference/#DocumenterTypst.DocumenterTypst","page":"API Reference","title":"DocumenterTypst.DocumenterTypst","text":"DocumenterTypst\n\nA Documenter.jl plugin for generating documentation in Typst/PDF format.\n\nUsage\n\nusing Documenter\nusing DocumenterTypst\n\nmakedocs(\n    sitename = \"MyPackage\",\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(),\n    pages = [\n        \"Home\" => \"index.md\",\n    ]\n)\n\nSee the documentation for DocumenterTypst.Typst for more options.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"module"},{"location":"api/reference/#DocumenterTypst.TypstWriter.Typst","page":"API Reference","title":"DocumenterTypst.TypstWriter.Typst","text":"DocumenterTypst.Typst(; kwargs...)\n\nOutput format specifier that results in Typst/PDF output. Used together with Documenter.makedocs, e.g.\n\nmakedocs(\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst()\n)\n\nThe makedocs argument sitename will be used for the document title. The authors argument should also be specified and will be used for the document metadata. A version number can be specified with the version option to Typst, which will be  printed in the document and also appended to the output PDF file name.\n\nKeyword arguments\n\nplatform sets the platform where the Typst file is compiled. Available options:\n\"typst\" (default): Uses Typst_jll, a Julia binary wrapper that automatically  provides the Typst compiler across all platforms.\n\"native\": Uses the system-installed typst executable found in PATH, or  a custom path specified via the typst keyword argument.\n\"docker\": Uses Docker to compile the Typst file. Requires docker to be  available in PATH.\n\"none\": Skips compilation and only generates the .typ source file in the  build directory.\nversion specifies the version number printed on the title page of the manual. Defaults to the value in the TRAVIS_TAG environment variable (although this behaviour  is considered deprecated), or to an empty string if TRAVIS_TAG is unset.\ntypst allows specifying a custom path to a typst executable. Only used when  platform=\"native\". Can be either a String path or a Cmd object.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/reference/#DocumenterTypst.TypstWriter","page":"API Reference","title":"DocumenterTypst.TypstWriter","text":"A module for rendering Document objects to Typst and PDF.\n\nKeywords\n\nTypstWriter uses the following additional keyword arguments that can be passed to Documenter.makedocs: authors, sitename.\n\nsitename is the site's title displayed in the title bar and at the top of the navigation menu. It goes into the Typst document title.\n\nauthors can be used to specify the authors. It goes into the Typst document metadata.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"module"},{"location":"#DocumenterTypst.jl","page":"Home","title":"DocumenterTypst.jl","text":"Fast, modern PDF generation for Julia documentation.\n\nDocumenterTypst.jl is a Documenter.jl plugin that generates high-quality PDF documentation using the Typst typesetting system.","category":"section"},{"location":"#Why-DocumenterTypst?","page":"Home","title":"Why DocumenterTypst?","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#Lightning-Fast","page":"Home","title":"âš¡ Lightning Fast","text":"< 90 seconds to compile the full Julia documentation (vs several minutes with LaTeX)\nPowered by Typst's incremental compilation engine","category":"section"},{"location":"#Beautiful-Output","page":"Home","title":"ðŸŽ¨ Beautiful Output","text":"Modern, professional typography\nConsistent styling across all platforms\nHigh-quality PDF output optimized for both screen and print","category":"section"},{"location":"#Easy-Setup","page":"Home","title":"ðŸ”§ Easy Setup","text":"No LaTeX distribution required\nWorks out of the box with Typst_jll.jl\nCross-platform support (Linux, macOS, Windows)","category":"section"},{"location":"#Flexible-Math-Support","page":"Home","title":"ðŸ§® Flexible Math Support","text":"LaTeX math via mitex for backward compatibility\nNative Typst math for new projects\nSeamless integration with existing Documenter documentation","category":"section"},{"location":"#Production-Ready","page":"Home","title":"ðŸŽ¯ Production Ready","text":"Built on stable Documenter internal APIs (same as DocumenterVitepress)\nComprehensive test coverage (133+ tests)\nActive maintenance and community support","category":"section"},{"location":"#Quick-Example","page":"Home","title":"Quick Example","text":"using Documenter\nusing DocumenterTypst\n\nmakedocs(\n    sitename = \"MyPackage\",\n    authors = \"Your Name\",\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(),\n    pages = [\n        \"Home\" => \"index.md\",\n        \"API\" => \"api.md\",\n    ]\n)\n\nThis generates a professional PDF with table of contents, cross-references, syntax highlighting, and more.","category":"section"},{"location":"#Installation","page":"Home","title":"Installation","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(\"DocumenterTypst\")","category":"section"},{"location":"#Features-at-a-Glance","page":"Home","title":"Features at a Glance","text":"Feature Status\nFast Compilation âœ…\nLaTeX Math âœ…\nTypst Math âœ…\nCode Blocks âœ…\nTables âœ…\nImages âœ…\nCross-References âœ…\nAdmonitions âœ…\nFootnotes âœ…\nTable of Contents âœ…\nCustom Templates âœ…\nMulti-page Docs âœ…","category":"section"},{"location":"#Comparison-with-LaTeX-Backend","page":"Home","title":"Comparison with LaTeX Backend","text":" DocumenterTypst Documenter (LaTeX)\nCompilation Time < 90s (Julia docs) Several minutes\nSetup Zero-config Requires LaTeX distribution\nFile Size Compact Compact\nOutput Quality High High\nMath Support LaTeX + Typst LaTeX only\nError Messages Clear and helpful Sometimes cryptic\nIncremental Builds âœ… Fast âŒ Slow","category":"section"},{"location":"#Next-Steps","page":"Home","title":"Next Steps","text":"Pages = [\n    \"manual/getting_started.md\",\n    \"manual/configuration.md\",\n    \"examples/basic.md\",\n]\nDepth = 1","category":"section"},{"location":"#Community","page":"Home","title":"Community","text":"GitHub: lucifer1004/DocumenterTypst.jl\nIssues: Report bugs or request features\nDiscussions: Share your experience and ask questions","category":"section"},{"location":"#Acknowledgments","page":"Home","title":"Acknowledgments","text":"DocumenterTypst.jl builds upon:\n\nDocumenter.jl - The Julia documentation generator\nTypst - Modern typesetting system\nmitex - LaTeX math in Typst\nDocumenterVitepress.jl - Inspiration for the plugin architecture","category":"section"},{"location":"#License","page":"Home","title":"License","text":"MIT License. See LICENSE for details.","category":"section"}]
